-- German Solar Panel Installations to Hit Record, FAZ Says
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t
-- 2012-03-08T20:27:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-08/german-solar-panel-installations-to-hit-record-frankfurter-says.html
Solar panel installations in Germany
will probably reach a record 8,000 megawatts this year,
 Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung  reported, citing the DIHK
national industry and trade chambers,  The government’s reductions in subsidies for solar power
aren’t sufficient to prevent an increase in demand for panels,
the newspaper cited Martin Wansleben, managing director at the
DIHK, as saying in an interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicholas Comfort in Frankfurt at 
 ncomfort1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at 
 fconnelly@bloomberg.net  